This page provides a list of the FHIR artifacts defined as part of this implementation guide.


Structures: Resource Profiles {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR resources for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               HL7® AT Core Organization Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for organization data in Austria.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               HL7® AT Core Patient Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for patient data in Austria.
The HL7® AT Core Patient is based upon the core FHIR® Patient Resource and designed to meet the applicable patient demographic data elements in Austria. It identifies which core elements, extensions, vocabularies and value sets SHALL be present in the resource when using this profile. Note, this extension represents the common structure of Patient information within Austrian information systems.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               HL7® AT Core Practitioner Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for practitioner data in Austria.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               HL7® AT Core PractitionerRole Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for practitioner role data in Austria.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               HL7® AT Core ValueSet Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for valuesets in Austria.
The HL7® AT Core ValueSet is based upon the core FHIR® ValueSet Resource and defines the use of the OID extension.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Structures: Data Type Profiles {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               HL7® AT Core Address Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile for address data in Austria. Note, this extension represents the common structure of address information within Austrian information systems. This extension does not restrict the documented information to Austrian adresses. Address information that does not fit into the given structure may be captured by [Address Additional Information](StructureDefinition-at-core-ext-address-additionalInformation.html).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               HL7® AT Core ExtendedContactDetail Profile

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Profile to use the profile for address data in Austria on the datatype ExtendedContactDetail.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Structures: Extension Definitions {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               Address Additional Information

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Extension for the additional information part of the Austrian address.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Administrative Gender Addition

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Extension for the administrative gender of a person (Patient, Practitioner, ...). 
The extension is used to add the missing codes and is applied in case the code for administrative gender itself is set to 'other'.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Patient Religion

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Extension for the religion (registered in Austria) of a patient.
The extension is used to encode the religious confession of a patient (only confessions registered in Austria). Furthermore, it uses the official [HL7 AT CodeSystem](https://termpub.gesundheit.gv.at:443/TermBrowser/gui/main/main.zul?loadType=CodeSystem&loadName=HL7 AT ReligionAustria) for religion and is therefore aligned with the ELGA ValueSet, respectively.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               System OID

            {% capture desc %}HL7® Austria FHIR® Core Extension for the capturing of OID in ValueSets to reference the CodeSystem they come from.
The extension is used to document the OID of the system of a code referenced in a ValueSet, to align FHIR with the HL7 Austria CDA document guidelines.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





